2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 SUBCOMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
FOR
4 HOUSE BILL NO. 3324 By: Osburn
5
6
7 SUBCOMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
8 An Act relating to public health and safety;
establishing the requirements the platform is
9 required to have; creating the Oklahoma Statewide
Health Platform Revolving Fund; stating the purpose;
10 providing for codification; providing an effective
date; and declaring an emergency.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-103.1 of Title 63, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 The Oklahoma Statewide Health Platform Revolving Fund in Section
19 2 of this act shall be used exclusively to contract for and
20 implement a statewide, enterprise-wide, cloud-based communication,
21 and care coordination Health Insurance Portability and
22 Accountability Act (HIPAA)-compliant platform that:
23 1. Provides every licensed hospital, Emergency Management
24 Services (EMS) agency, and public health entity in the State of
Req. No. 16445 Page 1

1 Okla homa with real-time, HIPAA-compliant team alerting, live video
2 consultation, electrocardiogram (ECG) and image sharing, patient
3 channeling, and mass casualty and multiple casualty incident
4 management for time-sensitive emergencies including stroke, ST-
5 elevation myocardial infarction (STEMI), trauma, sepsis, cardiac
6 arrest, respiratory failure, pediatric emergencies, other general
7 emergencies, and natural disasters; and
8 2. Creates one unified operating platform connecting all
9 emergency response entities across the entire state.
10 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-103.2 of Title 63, unless
12 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 There is hereby created in the State Treasury, a revolving fund
14 for the Oklahoma State Department of Health to be designated the
15 "Oklahoma Statewide Health Platform Revolving Fund". The fund shall
16 be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and
17 shall consist of all monies received by the Oklahoma State
18 Department of Health from state-appropriated funds, federal funds,
19 donations, grants, and contributions from any public or private
20 source and designated for the purpose set forth in this section.
21 All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby
22 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma State
23 Department of Health for the purpose provided for in Section 1 of
24 this act. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon warrants
Req. No. 16445 Page 2

1 issu ed by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
2 law with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
3 Services for approval and payment.
4 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
5 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
6 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
7 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
8 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
